'''Márcio Salomão Brazão da Rosa''' ({{IPA|pt|ˈmaɾ.si.u sɐ.lu.ˈmɐ̃w bɾɐ.ˈzɐ̃w dɐ ˈʀɔ.zɐ|lang}}; born 23 February 1997) is a Cape Verdean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[First Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|Bulgarian First League]] club [[PFC Montana|Montana]] and the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

==Professional career==
Rosa began playing football at the age of 8 with ''Escola de Preparação Integral de Futebol'' in Cape Verde. He moved to the Portuguese club [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]] in 2015, and after a year in the youth academy joined [[C.D.C. Montalegre|Montalegre]] on loan in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.criolosports.com/index.php/criolos-no-estrangeiro/1604-criolos-no-estrangeiro-marcio-da-rosa-emprestado-pelo-chaves-ao-montalegre|title=Criolos no Estrangeiro: Márcio da Rosa emprestado pelo chaves ao Montalegre|website=www.criolosports.com}}</ref>

==International career==
Rosa was called up to represent the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]] in May 2018 for two international friendlies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/detalhe/cabo-verde-marcio-rosa-chamado-a-selecao.html|title=Cabo Verde: Márcio Rosa chamado à seleção|first=João|last=Seixas|publisher=}}</ref> He made his debut in a 0-0 (4-3) penalty shootout win over [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] on 3 June 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/jogo/andorra-vs-cabo-verde-434344|title=Andorra vs Cabo Verde - SAPO Desporto|first=|last=SAPO|publisher=}}</ref> He was named in the roster for the [[Africa Cup of Nations|2021 Africa Cup of Nations]] when the team reached the round of 16.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/cape-verde-islands/story/4555552/cape-verde-include-veteran-quartet-for-afcon|title=Cape Verde include veteran quartet for AFCON|publisher=[[ESPN]]|date=23 December 2021}}</ref>

